quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  23,1,"The believers have indeed attained true success:",footnotes:179389:1
  23,2,"those who, in their Prayers, humble themselves;",footnotes:179390:1,footnotes:179391:2
  23,3,"who avoid whatever is vain and frivolous;",footnotes:179392:1
  23,4,"who observe Zakah;",footnotes:179393:1
  23,5,"who strictly guard their private parts",footnotes:179394:1
  23,6,"save from their wives, or those whom their right hands possess; for with regard to them they are free from blame ""
  23,7,"As for those who seek beyond that, they are transgressors"",footnotes:179395:1
  23,8,"who are true to their trusts and their covenants,",footnotes:179396:1
  23,9,"and who guard their Prayers.",footnotes:179397:1
  23,10,"Such are the inheritors"